<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLOTHESLINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARYLOU LUTHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Q: What do you recommend as a wrap for a strapless white sequined prom dress? 
My mom sews. 
</P>
<P>
-- K.H. 
</P>
<P>
A: A white organza shawl would be a simple-to-make, safe choice. But if you're 
willing to be a little daring, how about wearing an oversized white organza 
shirt? Londoner Rifat Ozbek designed one with kimono sleeves. You can 
approximate the look with Vogue Pattern 7727 (illustrated here). It has French 
cuffs, but essentially it's the same. MARYLOU LUTHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Drawing, Wrap / FERNANDO FLORES 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA021690-0035 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 177043 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 16, 1990, Friday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
View; Part E; Page 11; Column 1; View Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
