are being worked out at this moment so we can't really talk specifically what 
they are about." CBS' official announcement of the signing of Zahn -- at an 
estimated $1-million salary -- has been delayed by the formality of ABC's 
contractual option to make a matching counteroffer. Sources said that ABC was 
unlikely to match CBS' offer, but Zahn's hiring by CBS has been held up because 
ABC News executives have been in South Africa. Faith Daniels will be the 
substitute host on "CBS This Morning" next week. BETH KLEID 
