The U.N.'s Food and Agriculture Organization repeated a warning that 1.1 
million tons of grain will be needed to ward off starvation threatening 4 
million people in Ethiopia. House-to-house fighting was reported between 
Eritrean rebels and government troops battling for control of Massawa. Heavy 
casualties on both sides were reported. 
