<HEADLINE>
<P>
WAVES' GEORGESON SERIOUSLY INJURED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mark Georgeson, a sophomore center on Pepperdine's basketball team, suffered a 
broken pelvis and three broken ribs in an auto accident early Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Georgeson was in serious but stable condition at Westlake Community Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
The school said Georgeson was involved in a head-on collision while driving to 
his Calabasas home through Malibu Canyon after the Waves' game at Loyola 
Marymount Wednesday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
