<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mark McGwire of the Oakland Athletics signed a one-year, $1.5-million contract, 
avoiding arbitration. 
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old first baseman also received a number of incentive bonuses 
totaling $195,000. 
</P>
<P>
McGwire had asked $1.72 million and the A's had offered $1 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
