<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOROS HIT THE ROAD LOOKING FOR BERTH IN CCAA TOURNEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Dominguez Hills men's basketball team faces a road trip this 
weekend that could determine whether it will win a berth in the California 
Collegiate Athletic Assn. post-season tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The Toros (5-5 in conference play and 9-14 overall) play at first-place 
Bakersfield (8-2, 20-3) tonight at 7:30. 
</P>
<P>
Then they visit Cal Poly San Luis Obispo (5-5, 15-8) on Saturday night at 8:05. 
</P>
<P>
Bakersfield is ranked No. 14 in the country. Cal Poly and Dominguez Hills are 
among four teams tied for third place in the CCAA, behind Bakersfield and UC 
Riverside (7-3, 17-6). 
</P>
<P>
Only four teams will advance to the conference tournament. A victory at San 
Luis Obispo would give the Toros a tie-breaker advantage because they defeated 
the Mustangs, 58-56, earlier in the season. Also tied for third are Cal State 
Los Angeles (5-5, 12-11), defeated twice this year by the Toros, and Cal State 
Northridge (5-5, 10-13), which beat Dominguez Hills twice. 
</P>
<P>
In women's play, the Lady Toros (3-6, 11-12) can keep their slim post-season 
hopes alive with a victory Saturday night at San Luis Obispo (4-4, 10-12). Game 
time is 5:45. 
</P>
