<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' SOCCER ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
HART-BUENA MATCH CALLED AFTER 2-2 TIE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After playing through four overtime periods and two sets of five-shot, 
penalty-kick shoot-outs, Hart and Buena highs were forced to call their 
Southern Section 3-A Division first-round boys' soccer playoff match at Hart on 
Thursday because of darkness with the score tied, 2-2. 
</P>
<P>
The score was tied, 1-1, after regulation. Buena scored in the first 10-minute 
extra period, and Hart scored in the second 10-minute overtime. 
</P>
<P>
They followed with two scoreless 10-minute sudden-death periods, then two sets 
of five penalty kicks. After 3 hours 15 minutes, the match was postponed. 
</P>
<P>
In another match: 
</P>
<P>
San Marcos 1, Burbank 0 -- San Marcos scored early in the second half to knock 
visiting Burbank (12-5-6) out of the Southern Section 3-A playoffs. 
</P>
