<P>
SYKES DROPPED FROM BASKETBALL TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FULLERTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John Sykes, Cal State Fullerton's starting center at the beginning of the 
season, has been dropped from the team, Fullerton Coach John Sneed said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
"John Sykes is through for the year," Sneed said. "He missed the team meeting 
yesterday and hasn't been attending study hall." 
</P>
<P>
Sykes had missed six games this season because of disciplinary suspensions or 
illness, and had not been expected to play any more this season even if he was 
with the team. 
</P>
<P>
"I gave him the benefit of the doubt but he hasn't turned his ways around," 
Sneed said. ROBYN NORWOOD 
