<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-MARINA PLAYER GEORGESON INJURED IN AUTO ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KOLLEN LONG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mark Georgeson, a sophomore center on the Pepperdine basketball team and a 
former Marina High School player, was seriously injured early Thursday in a 
head-on collision while driving in Malibu Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
Georgeson suffered a broken pelvis and three broken ribs. 
</P>
<P>
He was listed in serious but stable condition Thursday afternoon at Westlake 
Community Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred as Georgeson was driving from Pepperdine to his residence 
in Calabasas after Wednesday night's game against Loyola Marymount. A 
spokeswoman for the California Highway Patrol said Georgeson, 20, was driving 
north on Malibu Canyon Road when he went into the southbound lane and collided 
with a car driven by Parkie Singh, 52, of Malibu. Singh was listed in critical 
but stable condition at Westlake Community Hospital Thursday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
A CHP spokeswoman said a ticket probably would not be issued. 
</P>
<P>
The 6-foot-10 Georgeson, a 1987 graduate of Marina High in Huntington Beach, 
has started 17 games this season and is averaging four points and 2.5 rebounds. 
He spent the 1987-88 season as a redshirt at Arizona and transferred to 
Pepperdine in December of 1988. KOLLEN LONG 
</P>
</TEXT>
