<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: DISTRIBUTED LOGIC POSTS A PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Distributed Logic Corp., the Anaheim computer products company, posted a net 
income of $18,641 for fiscal 1989, contrasted with a loss of $2.2 million for 
the year before. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue for the year ended Oct. 31 rose slightly, to $51.5 million from $51.2 
million. 
</P>
<P>
For the fourth quarter of 1989, however, the company reported a net loss of 
$15,675, contrasted with a loss of $1.9 million for the period in 1988. Revenue 
increased 19%, to $13.5 million from $11.4 million. 
</P>
<P>
Glenn C. Salley, Distributed chairman and chief executive, said net income was 
adversely affected by interest expense, foreign currency translation losses and 
unfavorable international tax charges. 
</P>
<P>
"Although this resulted in a net loss for the fourth quarter, we were 
profitable for the full year, which is a significant improvement over the prior 
two fiscal years," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
