<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOCUS: 28TH STREET MARINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Newcomb Development's $30-million project will be the first to combine 
commercial and residential uses on the Newport Beach waterfront. The 28th 
Street Marina will include 35 condominiums, 22,000 square feet of commercial 
and retail space, underground parking spaces and 21 private boat docks for 
lease. 
</P>
<P>
Grading has begun on the two-acre site, and completion of the complex is 
expected in early 1991. Offices and shops will occupy the ground floor, with 
residences on the second and third floors. Among the other features are a 
bayfront promenade and a courtyard in the center of the site. 
</P>
<P>
FACTS AND FIGURES 
</P>
<P>
Address: Balboa Peninsula bayfront 
</P>
<P>
Developer: Newcomb Development 
</P>
<P>
Architect: Stockton-Hidey Associates, Irvine 
</P>
<P>
Primary Contractor: Newcomb Development 
</P>
<P>
Use: Commercial, retail and residential 
</P>
<P>
Cost: $30 million 
</P>
<P>
Scheduled completion date: Early 1991 
</P>
<P>
Parking capacity: 189 
</P>
<P>
Source: Ann Romano Associates 
</P>
