<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ropak Corp.: The Fullerton maker of plastic packaging and handling products 
said that 1989 net income dropped to $807,000 from $2.9 million a year ago, 
despite a 6% gain in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
The company blamed the decrease on intense competition, a rise in costs and 
unused production capacity that resulted from the company's expansion. Revenue 
for the year rose to $94.4 million from $88.8 million. For the fourth quarter, 
Ropak lost $97,000; it reported a net income of $493,000 for the period in 
1988. Revenue declined 5%, to $20.5 million from $21.6 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
