<HEADLINE>
<P>
ABC SIGNS JAMES L. BROOKS TO EXCLUSIVE CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABC made its long-simmering deal with Emmy- and Oscar-winning 
writer-producer-director James L. Brooks official Thursday, announcing that it 
had signed him to an exclusive contract under which his company, Gracie Films, 
will develop at least three comedy series for the network. 
</P>
<P>
Gracie Films will continue to produce "The Tracey Ullman Show" and "The 
Simpsons" for Fox Broadcasting. 
</P>
<P>
Unlike ABC's exclusive deal with writer-producer Steven Bochco ("Doogie Howser, 
M.D."), Brooks' does not specify any time constraints on when the projects must 
be developed. 
</P>
<P>
"We want their best work," Robert Iger, president of ABC Entertainment, said of 
Brooks and his associates, "and (we) feel that this agreement, free of the 
usual time strictures, should prove fruitful for both organizations." 
</P>
<P>
Brooks was co-creator of "The Mary Tyler Moore Show" and wrote and produced the 
films "Terms of Endearment" and "Broadcast News." 
</P>
</TEXT>
