<P>
BILLY IDOL HAS 4TH OPERATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
British rock star Billy Idol was listed in fair condition Thursday after 
undergoing a fourth operation on his right leg, broken in a motorcycle accident 
eight days ago, his press agent said. 
</P>
<P>
Idol, 34, was driving home without a helmet after having finished recording an 
album, "Charmed Life," when his Harley-Davidson motorcycle was involved in a 
collision with a car, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Idol, whose hits include "White Wedding" and "Dancing with Myself," is expected 
to be in the hospital another two weeks, press agent Ellen Golden added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
