NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
LEONA: 'IVANA MODELED AFTER ME' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Convicted hotel queen Leona Helmsley believes that Donald J. Trump modeled his 
estranged wife, Ivana, after her and says she wouldn't believe the billionaire 
real estate tycoon even "if his tongue were notarized." 
</P>
<P>
In an interview scheduled to be published in the Daily News on Sunday, the 
president of Helmsley Hotels said Trump is "obsessed with me." 
</P>
<P>
"He modeled his wife after me. Really," she was quoted as saying, noting that 
Trump had made his wife president of New York's Plaza Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
"When Ivana first came into my bedroom years ago, she called Scalamandre Silks 
the next day and told them she wanted everything exactly the way I had it." 
</P>
<P>
Helmsley, who is appealing her federal tax fraud conviction, observed that 
Trump's hate for her is reflected in an interview in the March Playboy magazine 
in which he described Helmsley as "a vicious, horrible woman who systematically 
destroyed the Helmsley name." 
</P>
<P>
"Then why does he model his wife after me?" Helmsley asked. "I wouldn't believe 
Trump if his tongue was notarized." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Leona Helmsley 
