<P>
BLEDSOE MERIT SCHOLAR FINALIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tempestt Bledsoe, the 16-year-old actress who plays Vanessa Huxtable on "The 
Cosby Show," has become a finalist for a National Merit Scholarship, her 
publicist said. 
</P>
<P>
The nationwide academic scholarship is awarded on the basis of students' 
academic record and scores on the PSAT, a scholastic aptitude examination, 
according to a statement issued Thursday by publicist David Brokaw. 
</P>
<P>
Bledsoe has studied at the Professional Children's School in New York City. She 
is graduating from high school with straight A's, Brokaw said. 
</P>
